# AI Privacy Pipeline Rules

- Never commit raw videos, extracted frames, faces, license plates, or unblurred screenshots.
- Run anonymization before urban-object detection.
- Detection output must contain only object type, latitude, longitude, confidence, and timestamp.
- Do not add identity recognition, profiling, person tracking, vehicle tracking, or license plate OCR.
- Keep model artifacts and raw media outside Git history.
- Document raw-data deletion with `scripts/delete_raw_data.py` before final delivery.

